surv_strategy: I went all in with shares in the first or second round. Actually,I  might have left a little cash to build up some cash reserves in the first 5 rounds. But I remember that at least from Round 5, I started buying every time I collected enough for a single share. I knew that it was essential to buy-in before Round 10. I had concerns that the peak would happen around Round 15, but I jumped the gun a bit. I could have held out longer for about 12% higher sale prices, but I wanted to unload my entire holdings before the peak. I was concerned that if the market fell flat, then finding a buyer would become increasingly difficult and I might have to sacrifice more than I might stand to gain by holding out for those final few points. I think I was all cash by Round 20 and I collected only from the 5% interest each round.

If I could suggest an improvement to the dashboard, I felt that the experiment could be more exciting if there were a scoreboard so that players could know their standing in terms of total net worth. It was nice to play with other users, but the interactions felt quite empty. This is just wishful thinking because I find that competition brings out the best in my performance. I would settle for a final scoreboard so that I could learn my relative performance on the final screen.
